  m_Name: Amonite
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishData
  <fishName>k__BackingField: Amonite
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "Ammonites were coiled, shelled creatures that ruled
    the ancient seas for over 300 million years, living alongside dinosaurs before
    vanishing in the same mass extinction. Their beautiful spiral shells \u2014 found
    as fossils on every continent \u2014 grew in a mathematically perfect spiral
    called the golden ratio. They were so abundant that scientists use their fossils
    as a clock to date ancient rock layers. "
